result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicole Kristen Phillips was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nicole Kristen Phillips in court with attorney Debra Jeanne Patterson.  Defendant Nicole Kristen Phillips in custody.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

Statements made as to sentencing by State, Defense and Defendant.

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of THIRTY (30) MONTHS, with credit for ONE HUNDRED NINETY-SIX (196) DAYS time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is TWELVE (12) MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is EIGHTEEN (18) MONTHS.  The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program (Boot Camp) and IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of TWO (2) YEARS.  ALL TERMS ARE CONCURRENT TO 14CF5457.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION/PROBATION:

* Court ordered the defendant to serve SIX (6) MONTHS in the House of Correction.  STAYED.  To be used at agent's discretion.  Huber for child care, treatment and employment (if employed).
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol. 
* Random urine screens.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered.
* Court ordered Defendant's motor vehicle operating privileges SUSPENDED for a period of SIX (6) MONTHS.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.

The Court ordered that all court costs, fees and surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment WITH tax intercept or other means.
